<br>
Also any form of direct heal will affect clerics (and no, we are not the most wanted class outside raids, a shaman can replace a cleric anywhere except CT and second floor Ssra if they run into a elite with slow. A druid cant replace a cleric as easy as a shaman but they do replace a cleric rather easy in 80% of the zones) when it come to doing something outside of the raid. The raid is our bread and butter due to CH but that is also all we do bring (1 cleric for Aego every 2.5h assuming they did not get AA buff skill). Outside a raid so is CH something you need to cast on the tank every 4+ mobs if even that (fear break in with 1 group, I casted 1 divine light during the first 30 min and that was all my healing on a full spawn fear. Ssra? I can go afk and they live when I come back 10 min later). So why am I here? Because either so are all classes excluding most of the druids posting completly insane and druids are severly crippled and can barly do anything or so are druids now reaching the end game and suddently cant dot/heal the MT etc as they thought they should. They are looking for a role in highlevel raids but cant fit in one roll easy and directly see wow, this was great difference. Most druids say we aint needed, well not needed as in the raid wont happend if you aint there but you are damn handy to have around! Lack wizards? Let the druids nuke. Lack healing power? Let the druid help healing. Mage lom doing rods? Let the druid do the ds. So there is not one given role in a high level raid for a druid but it do what it always have done, it fills in what ever gaps there is. Does that mean a druid can be replaced? Yup. That is a price payed by beeing able to take on several different roles in the highend game but not beeing master on any of them.<br>
